Subject: [PATCH 1501/1722] drm/amdgpu: disallow foreign BOs in the display
 path
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Pinning them in other devices VRAM would obviously not work.

Signed-off-by: Christian KÃ¶nig <christian.koenig@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Ayyappa Ch <ayyappa.chandolu@amd.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_display.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_display.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_display.c
index 3573ffb..811299b 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_display.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_display.c
@@ -211,6 +211,12 @@ int amdgpu_crtc_page_flip(struct drm_crtc *crtc,
 	obj = new_amdgpu_fb->obj;
 	new_abo = gem_to_amdgpu_bo(obj);
 
+	if (new_rbo->adev != adev) {
+		DRM_ERROR("Foreign BOs not allowed in the display engine\n");
+		r = -EINVAL;
+		goto cleanup;
+	}
+
 	/* pin the new buffer */
 	r = amdgpu_bo_reserve(new_abo, false);
 	if (unlikely(r != 0)) {
